 and was educated at <school wordnetid="108276720" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../228/53228.xml">
Eton College</link></school>
. Brett later claimed that he was an "academic disaster" at Eton and attributed his learning difficulties to <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../305/8305.xml">
dyslexia</link>. However, he excelled at singing and was a member of the college choir.</p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
Acting career</st>
<p>

Brett trained as an actor at the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../537/523537.xml">
Central School of Speech and Drama</link> in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../867/17867.xml">
London</link></village>
.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> He made his professional acting debut at the <structure wordnetid="104341686" confidence="0.8">
<building wordnetid="102913152" confidence="0.8">
<artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
<theater wordnetid="104417809" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../806/749806.xml">
Library Theatre</link></theater>
</artifact>
</building>
</structure>
 in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../206/20206.xml">
Manchester</link></village>
 in 1954, and made his London stage debut with the <theater wordnetid="104417809" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../824/589824.xml">
Old Vic</link></theater>
 company in <it>Troilus and Cressida</it> 1956.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref> In the same year he appeared on Broadway as the Duke of Aumerle in <it>Richard II</it>.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%223%22])">3</ref> He went on to play many classical roles on stage, including numerous <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<poet wordnetid="110444194" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<writer wordnetid="110794014" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<dramatist wordnetid="110030277" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../897/32897.xml">
Shakespearean</link></dramatist>
</writer>
</actor>
</poet>
</person>
 parts in his early career with the <theater wordnetid="104417809" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../824/589824.xml">
Old Vic</link></theater>
 and later with the <theater wordnetid="104417809" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../775/167775.xml">
Royal National Theatre</link></theater>
. Brett made his first television appearance in 1954 and his first feature film appearance in 1955.</p>
